%% Mermaid diagram describing the ghost-management API request flow
flowchart TD
    Client([API Client])
    Routes{{`routes/api.php`}}
    AuthController[[`AuthController`]]
    EventController[[`EventController`]]
    AttendeeController[[`AttendeeController`]]
    RequestValidator[[`EventRequest`<br/>`AttendeeRequest`]]
    Policy[[`EventPolicy`<br/>`AttendeePolicy`]]
    Model[[`Event`<br/>`Attendee`<br/>`User`]]
    Resource[[`EventResource`<br/>`AttendeeResource`<br/>`UserResource`]]
    DB[(SQLite / Database)]
    Sanctum[Sanctum Auth]

    Client -->|HTTP request| Routes
    Routes -->|POST /login| AuthController
    Routes -->|POST /logout| AuthController
    Routes -->|GET /user| Sanctum
    Routes -->|apiResource events| EventController
    Routes -->|apiResource events.attendees| AttendeeController
    
    AuthController -->|Validates credentials| Model
    AuthController -->|Creates token| Sanctum
    AuthController -->|Returns token| Client
    
    EventController -->|Validates input| RequestValidator
    EventController -->|Checks authorization| Policy
    EventController -->|Reads/Writes| Model
    EventController -->|Transforms data| Resource
    EventController -->|Returns JSON| Client
    
    AttendeeController -->|Validates input| RequestValidator
    AttendeeController -->|Checks authorization| Policy
    AttendeeController -->|Reads/Writes| Model
    AttendeeController -->|Transforms data| Resource
    AttendeeController -->|Returns JSON| Client
    
    Model -->|Eloquent ORM| DB
    Sanctum -->|Validates token| Model

